definition.value: A recombinant viral vaccine vector that uses PVSRIPO, a recombinant nonpathogenic polio-rhinovirus chimera. PVSRIPO is an engineerable oncolytic virus whereas its internal ribosomal entry site element can be substituted to demolish its cytopathogenic effect. PVSRIPO has a natural inherent tropism for antigen-presenting cells (including dendritic cells and macrophages) due to the presence of the CD-155 receptor on their cellular surfaces. This enables it of inducing CD8+ T-cell mediate immune responses.
